  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut each block of paneer into 12 cubes. Deseed and roughly\nchop the peppers. Scrape both into a mixing bowl. Add the oil\nand curry paste. Mix to coat the cheese and peppers in the paste."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get a large frying pan over a high heat. Tip in the paneer and\npeppers along with all the oil and paste. Spread out in the pan and\nfry for 5 mins, turning everything regularly with a spatula, until\nthe paneer is crisp on all sides."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, make a quick raita. Dollop the yogurt into a small bowl\nand tear in half the mint leaves. Coarsely grate in the cucumber,\nthen peel and finely grate in the garlic. Season with salt and black\npepper and stir."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Take the paneer off the heat when ready. Warm the chapattis or\nrotis in the microwave following the packet instructions and put\ntwo on each plate. Spoon over the tikka paneer and peppers,\nthen dollop over some raita and mango chutney. Tear over the\nremaining mint leaves to finish."
    }
  ],
